 :spec/constraints
 ["LLM stream extension is additive — chunks without :tool-use / :tool-result keys parse identically; existing :on-chunk consumers see no shape change. Verified by a fixture-replay test that runs the existing chat-stream consumer against a recorded event sequence and asserts the produced text/usage/stop-reason are unchanged"
  "Detectors stay pure reducers — observe takes (state, observation) and returns a state map with new anomalies appended; no detector reads from the event log, the LLM client, or any external state during observe (Stage 1 contract, preserved)"
  "Per-event detector overhead in the criterium benchmark stays under 5ms total across the framework's default detector set ([:tool-loop :repair-loop]) on a recorded event-fixture from the event-log-tool-visibility dogfood"
  "Anomaly evidence remains bounded per Stage 1 — no raw tool args, raw assistant text, or raw file content in evidence payloads. The Stage 2 always-hash redaction in event-envelope is preserved"
  "Detector wiring is agent-agnostic — the same agent.detector-wiring code path serves planner / implementer / reviewer / tester / curator / releaser. Per-agent overlays come from prompt EDN, not from N copies of the wiring"
  "Default behavior when prompt EDN omits :prompt/detectors: framework defaults [:tool-loop :repair-loop] with Stage 2 class-default policy. No prompt change required for an agent to gain detector coverage"
  "Per-category :on-anomaly resolution order: 1) controlling-anomaly category looked up in on-anomaly map; 2) fall back to (policy class); 3) fall back to :continue. Stage 2's 2-arity (handle policy anomalies) stays for back-compat — equivalent to (handle policy {} anomalies)"
  "Termination cancels the in-flight LLM stream via the existing chunk-callback :stop path. The controlling anomaly is recorded in the run's event log; agent.invoke throws an ex-info whose ex-data has :anomaly :anomalies.agent/terminated (the project-wide ex-data → anomaly category convention used by components/response) plus :controlling-anomaly <anomaly-map> carrying the full evidence payload. :anomaly/data is NOT used here — that key is the data slot on canonical anomaly maps, not on classification ex-info"
  "Removing all detectors via prompt EDN ({:detectors/defaults []}) leaves the agent functional and bounded by Layer 1 caps only — Stage 2's runtime null-detector fallback path covers this"
  "Tool-call-id from the CLI's tool_use block is the pairing key between :tool-use and :tool-result chunks. The agent layer keeps an open-tool-calls map keyed by id; events with no matching id are dropped (CLI gave us a result without a use, or vice versa)"]

 :spec/acceptance-criteria
 [;; LLM stream extension
  "parse-claude-stream-line emits :tool-call-id and :tool-input on tool_use content blocks — verified by fixture-replay test against a recorded Claude CLI stream"
  "parse-claude-stream-line emits a separate :tool-result chunk carrying :tool-call-id, :tool-output, :tool-error? on tool_result content blocks — verified by fixture-replay"
  "parse-codex-stream-line surfaces the same shape for the codex backend — fixture-replay over a recorded codex session"
  "Existing :on-chunk consumers (text/usage/stop-reason) see no shape change — fixture-replay test that runs the existing consumer against a recorded session and asserts produced state is byte-identical to a Stage 2 baseline"

  ;; agent.invoke wiring
  "agent.detector-wiring/with-detector-runtime builds a per-call runtime + normalizer, wraps :on-chunk to intercept tool-use/tool-result chunks, feeds Observations through the runtime, and on :terminate cancels the LLM stream — verified by integration test"
  "Each of planner, implementer, reviewer, tester, curator, releaser wraps its LLM call path in with-detector-runtime — verified by a structural test that grep-asserts every role-specific :invoke-fn calls with-detector-runtime"
  "agent.invoke wiring is shared — a code-search asserts a single agent.detector-wiring code path, not per-agent copies of detector + supervisor calls"

  ;; tool-loop fires on a real run
  "An agent that calls Read on the same path 6 times against the same :resource/version-hash terminates with :anomalies.agent/tool-loop (class :mechanical, severity :error) — integration test against a fake LLM client that produces the looping tool-use stream"
  "An agent that varies tool calls completes normally — integration test"

  ;; Per-agent overlays
  "A planner with prompt :prompt/detectors {:disable [:tool-loop]} does not fire that detector — integration test"
  "A reviewer with prompt :prompt/detectors {:on-anomaly {:anomalies.review/stagnation :warn}} produces a warn anomaly instead of terminating on stagnation — integration test"
  "A tester with :prompt/detectors {:tune {:tool-loop {:threshold-n 8}}} uses the bumped threshold — integration test"

  ;; Per-category :on-anomaly
  "supervisor/handle's 3-arity (handle policy on-anomaly anomalies) consults on-anomaly first; missing keys fall through to policy; missing class falls through to :continue — exhaustive truth-table test"
  "Stage 2's 2-arity (handle policy anomalies) is preserved and equivalent to (handle policy {} anomalies) — equivalence test against a recorded fixture of Stage 2 supervisor decisions"

  ;; Termination
  "On supervisor :terminate, the in-flight LLM stream is cancelled (the chunk-callback returns :stop) — integration test that asserts the stream consumer stops reading further chunks after termination"
  "On supervisor :terminate, agent.invoke throws an ex-info whose ex-data has :anomaly :anomalies.agent/terminated (the project-wide ex-data → anomaly classification convention used by components/response) plus :controlling-anomaly <anomaly-map> carrying the full controlling-anomaly payload — integration test asserts both keys are present and the controlling-anomaly map satisfies the canonical Anomaly schema"
  "All anomalies (controlling and not) emitted during a run are recorded in the run's event log — integration test that captures all emitted events and asserts both controlling and non-controlling anomalies are present"

  ;; Removing all detectors
  "An agent with prompt :prompt/detectors {:disable :all} (or {:detectors/defaults []}) runs to completion bounded only by Layer 1 caps — integration test"

  ;; Performance
  "Per-event detector overhead in the criterium benchmark stays under 5ms total across [:tool-loop :repair-loop] on the event-log-tool-visibility dogfood event-fixture (Stage 2 budget, preserved)"

  ;; Evidence bounding
  "Stage 2's fuzzer test (synthetic 'secret-shaped' content in agent inputs → no leakage in anomaly evidence) extends to cover :tool/output content surfaced through the new tool-result chunk path — verified by extending the fuzzer fixture"

  ;; Dogfood viability
  "A dogfood run on event-log-tool-visibility EITHER (a) completes through the full SDLC with no detector anomalies, OR (b) terminates with a detector-emitted anomaly that names which detector fired and includes reproducible evidence — verified by recording the run's event log and asserting it contains a :anomalies.agent/terminated event when termination occurred"]

