 :spec/priority
 {:tier        :critical
  :axes        #{:agent-quality :dogfood-enabler :supervision}
  :theme       :semantic-supervision
  :rationale   "Stages 1+2 shipped substrate + detectors but the runtime sits unconnected — :detector/tool-loop never fires on a real run. Stage 3 wires it up. After Stage 3 ships, every agent run goes through the detector pipeline and the supervisor can terminate on mechanical anomalies. The threshold-bump cycle (#779/#781/#782/#783) finally retires for the within-turn case. Stage 4 (phase contracts, full policy surface, more detectors) layers on top of a working detection pipeline; building it without Stage 3 would mean designing policy for a system that does not yet emit the events policy reacts to."
